## Security

- Never commit secrets; use `.env` files (gitignored) and `${ENV_VAR}` in MCP configs.
- Never manually edit `uv.lock` or `pnpm-lock.yaml` — use package managers.
- Ask before modifying CI workflows or Copier prompt defaults.

## Git Workflow

{% if changelog_module == 'enabled' %}Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/); commit-msg hooks enforce format when `quality_profile=strict`.
{% else %}Use clear, descriptive commit messages; enable changelog module for semantic-release automation.
{% endif %}

## Boundaries

<!-- agents-md:auto -->

### Always Do

{% if _python %}- Use `uv run` for Python commands
- Run quality checks before committing (`{{ _quality_cmd }}` or `uv run task quality`)
{% endif %}
- Update tests when changing behavior
- Keep docs module pages and AGENTS quick reference in sync when adding commands

### Ask First

- Adding dependencies to `pyproject.toml` or root `package.json`
- Modifying CI workflows or Copier answers
- Changing pre/post generation hooks in a template fork

### Never Touch

- `.env*` secrets
- Lock files (regenerate via uv/pnpm)
- `.copier-answers.yml` without understanding render impact

### Avoid

- Duplicating module docs inside AGENTS.md — link to `docs/modules/`
- Documenting commands for disabled modules
- Hand-editing Copier output then forgetting to update `.copier-answers.yml`

